The paper deals with opportunistic scheduling and beamforming schemes for MIMO-OFDMA downlink systems, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communication (cs.COM). However, since the paper focuses on reducing feedback in these systems, it is most likely to belong to the information theory (cs.IT) category.
